ntor-field-type-submit elementor-col-100 e-form__buttons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<button class=\"elementor-button elementor-size-sm\" type=\"submit\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Send<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/button>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/form>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-ebd3ab6 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"ebd3ab6\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-6f8a0c1\" data-id=\"6f8a0c1\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c9db489 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"c9db489\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-medium\"> What do wood cockroaches look like?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f9c978b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"f9c978b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Wood cockroaches are insects mostly found in wooded areas or around decaying trees. They have distinct appearances, making them easy to identify. Adult wood cockroaches typically range in size from 1\/2 to 7\/8-inch-long and are light brown with yellowish markings on their wings. They also have long antennae, which they use for sensory purposes.<\/p><p>One way to distinguish between male and female wood cockroaches is by looking at their wings. Males have longer wings extending beyond the tip of their abdomen, while females have shorter wings covering only about half of the abdomen. The males&#8217; longer wings serve as an adaptation for flying during mating season, whereas females mostly crawl on surfaces.<\/p><p>Despite their name, wood cockroaches do not infest homes like other common species of cockroach do. Instead, they prefer outdoor habitats and feed on decomposing plant matter like leaves and bark. While they may occasionally find their way indoors, they pose no significant threat to humans or property. They can easily be removed through simple exclusion methods, such as sealing cracks and building gaps.<\/p><p>Protect your home from wood cockroaches and\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/gnats\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><u><b>Gnats<\/b><\/u><\/a>\u00a0with our comprehensive pest control guide, while ensuring a comfortable environment.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a1e4412 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"a1e4412\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-medium\">Habitat, Diet, Lifecycle<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d5d9331 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"d5d9331\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Wood cockroaches are known to be forest-dwelling insects that thrive in decaying wood and leaf litter. They prefer to live in moist environments like rotting logs, stumps, and fallen branches. These types of cockroaches can also be found in homes with abundant firewood or untreated lumber.<\/p><p>The diet of a wood cockroach varies depending on their life stage. Nymphs feed on small insects, while adults prefer plant material such as fruit, leaves, and bark. Wood roaches have a slower lifecycle compared to other species of cockroaches. Their eggs hatch into nymphs that molt several times before reaching adulthood.<\/p><p>During winter, wood roaches enter a state called diapause, where they slow down their metabolism and remain dormant until spring arrives. This period helps them conserve energy during the colder months when food sources are scarce.<\/p><p>Overall, understanding the habitat, diet, and lifecycle of wood cockroaches is essential for pest control measures outdoors and indoors. Keeping areas dry and free from decaying matter inside your home or yard can help prevent these pests from invading your space.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-f2e545a elementor-section-full_width elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"f2e545a\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;,&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-5734248\" data-id=\"5734248\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-3045907\" data-id=\"3045907\" data-element_type=\"column\