ap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-14a13ae elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"14a13ae\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-639435a\" data-id=\"639435a\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-eb88333 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"eb88333\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-medium\">What can I do to protect myself from wood cockroaches?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-707285f elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"707285f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Wood cockroaches can be a nuisance in homes and gardens, but they are not as harmful as other types of roaches. However, these insects are kept from crawling around their living space. Here are some tips on how to protect yourself from wood cockroaches:<\/p><ul><li>Seal all cracks and gaps in windows, doors, and walls with silicone caulk or weather stripping to prevent them from entering your home.<\/li><li>Keep firewood piles away from the sides of buildings and off the ground as much as possible; this will reduce the number of hiding spots for wood cockroaches.<\/li><li>Clean gutters regularly to prevent debris buildup that can attract wood cockroaches.<\/li><li>Store trash cans far away from your house or garage; keep them tightly closed.<\/li><li>Remove any standing water around your home because it can attract pests like mosquitoes that could bring in additional problems, such as diseases or other pests like bed bugs or fleas.<\/li><\/ul><p>By following these simple steps, you can reduce the likelihood of having a wood cockroach infestation in your home while maintaining a clean and healthy environment for you and your family!<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Wood Cockroaches Identification Color Size Description Color In terms of color, wood cockroaches are light brown with yellowish markings on their wings. Size The wood cockroach typically measures around 7\/8 inches long. Description Wood Cockroach&#8217;s thorax has distinct lines parallel to their head and wingspan, which varies between males and females. These differences in size &#8230; <a title=\"Wood Cockroaches\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wood-cockroaches\/\" aria-label=\"More on Wood Cockroaches\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":6824,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"rank_math_lock_modified_date":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[14,37],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-6233","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-cockroach","category-pest-libraries"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6233"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies"